This is a simple example of what a "Back End" service might look like in the Rust programming language.

Right now it services a /login endpoint that returns a JWT token

To run this project:

1) Customize the .env file to your liking then run the following command:
$ . .env

2) Start the database server
$ docker-compose up -d

3) Run database migrations
$ cargo sqlx migrate run

4) Prepare the database server
$ cargo sqlx prepare

5) Run the API server
$ cargo run

You can use HTTPie (https://httpie.io/) to test it out:

$ http POST localhost:3000/login username=admin password=password
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
content-length: 181
content-type: application/json
date: Wed, 30 Oct 2024 23:21:28 GMT
{
    "token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJhZG1pbiIsImV4cCI6MTczMDMzNDA4OCwiaWF0IjoxNzMwMzMwNDg4fQ.oPfuz1bC4AW2q_d3Dh3BblJCLAGcnIvhhavIqVS8yNw",
    "token_type": "Bearer"
}
